Package: llmtextcoder
Title: Code and Judge Texts Against a Rubric Using an LLM
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Elad", "Zlotnick", email = "elad.zlotnick@mail.huji.ac.il", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1574-0135"))
Description: A generic engine for LLM-assisted qualitative text coding. Build
    a scoring prompt from a plain-text rubric template, send it to the OpenAI
    API with structured JSON output, and parse the model's reply into a flat
    data frame. Supports incremental batch scoring with automatic skip logic,
    per-row error handling, and full provenance tracking. Developed by
    HuppertLab at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem.
